 Use left ← and right arrow → keys to fine-tune selection.

instruction:
Click the slider to initialize. 

 Drag the slider to trace the ball along the curve. 

 Identify the point where the tangent line to the curve is *steepest* --- this is where the slope is at its maximum value. Look for where an imaginary straight line touching the curve would have the steepest upward angle. 

 Use left ← and right arrow → keys to fine-tune selection.
responsePrompt: The x-axis location of your click
